"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662968","Home Office","false","2017-01-19","<p>I am sorry but the data required to answer the question can only be provided at disproportionate cost. The government produces regular data on asylum as part of its Migration Statistics and the latest release can be found at:</p><p> </p><ul><li><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/572376/asylum2-q3-2016-tables.ods" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/572376/asylum2-q3-2016-tables.ods</a></li></ul><p> </p><ul><li><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/immigration-statistics-july-to-september-2016/returns#data-tables" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/immigration-statistics-july-to-september-2016/returns#data-tables</a></li></ul>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-01-19T13:34:34.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662968/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662968/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662968/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-20","Deportation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many enforced removals of failed asylum seekers were conducted in (a) Scotland, (b) England, (c) Wales and (d) Northern Ireland in each month since January 2016.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","58425"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662969","Home Office","false","2017-01-09","<p>In considering the proposal to extend the current contracts the Home Office listened carefully to a range of interested parties, including the evidence that has been given to the Home Affairs Committee and direct feedback from non-governmental organisations’ through regular engagement activity with various stakeholder groups. In extending the contracts the Home Office took the opportunity to make improvements to the contracts that address the concerns that have been raised. We will continue to work closely with a range of stakeholders to continue to improve the operation of the contracts.</p><p>No changes have been made in relation to the requirements and restrictions on room sharing and the contract continues to require our contractors to comply with national legislation and local authority rules.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","58478 ; 58479 ; 58480 ; 58482","2017-01-09T18:04:06.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662969/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662969/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662969/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-20","Asylum: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what consultations took place with the National Asylum Seekers stakeholder forum and other interested parties on changes to the sharing criteria of asylum accommodation contracts to allow children up to the age of 16 to share with their parents; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","58481"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662970","Home Office","false","2017-01-09","<p>The Home Office undertakes checks to confirm that potential candidates meet the eligibility requirements to work in the UK. However, the Home Office does not record the nationality of employees on our IT systems and is unable to provide this information.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-01-09T18:12:20.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662970/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662970/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662970/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-20","Home Office: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many (a) EU and (b) non-EU nationals are employed by (i) her Department, (ii) the UK Border Force and (iii) her Department's other agencies.","false","Biography information for Mr Pat McFadden","Wolverhampton South East","Mr Pat McFadden","58467"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662971","Home Office","false","2017-01-09","<p>In considering the proposal to extend the current contracts the Home Office listened carefully to a range of interested parties, including the evidence that has been given to the Home Affairs Committee and direct feedback from non-governmental organisations’ through regular engagement activity with various stakeholder groups. In extending the contracts the Home Office took the opportunity to make improvements to the contracts that address the concerns that have been raised. We will continue to work closely with a range of stakeholders to continue to improve the operation of the contracts.</p><p>No changes have been made in relation to the requirements and restrictions on room sharing and the contract continues to require our contractors to comply with national legislation and local authority rules.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","58478 ; 58479 ; 58480 ; 58481","2017-01-09T18:04:06.1Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662971/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662971/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662971/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-20","Asylum: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what consultations took place with the National Asylum Seekers stakeholder forum and other interested parties on changes to the sharing criteria in asylum accommodation contracts to allow willing mothers to use shared non-mother and baby unit accommodation; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","58482"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662972","Home Office","false","2017-01-09","<p>The Government has, and continues to, work closely with partners across Europe to ensure the timely and effective operation of the Dublin Regulation. We have seconded experts to France and Greece, and we have a long-standing secondee in Italy to support the work on unaccompanied asylum-seeking children in Europe, including the Dublin Regulation. The Government has transferred more than 750 children to the UK in support of the French operation to clear the Calais camp under both the family reunification provisions of the Dublin Regulation and the terms of section 67 of the Immigration Act 2016. Prior to the Calais camp clearance, between 1 January and 1 October, there were over 140 unaccompanied asylum seeking children accepted for transfer from Europe to the UK under the Dublin Regulation.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-01-09T18:15:27.423Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662972/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662972/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662972/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-20","Refugees: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what recent steps the Government has taken to speed up family reunification for unaccompanied refugee children in Europe.","false","Biography information for Sammy Wilson","East Antrim","Sammy Wilson","58466"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662973","Home Office","false","2017-01-09","<p>In considering the proposal to extend the current contracts the Home Office listened carefully to a range of interested parties, including the evidence that has been given to the Home Affairs Committee and direct feedback from non-governmental organisations’ through regular engagement activity with various stakeholder groups. In extending the contracts the Home Office took the opportunity to make improvements to the contracts that address the concerns that have been raised. We will continue to work closely with a range of stakeholders to continue to improve the operation of the contracts.</p><p>No changes have been made in relation to the requirements and restrictions on room sharing and the contract continues to require our contractors to comply with national legislation and local authority rules.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","58479 ; 58480 ; 58481 ; 58482","2017-01-09T18:04:05.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662973/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662973/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662973/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-20","Asylum: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what consultations took place with the National Asylum Seekers stakeholder forum and other interested parties on changing the sharing criteria in asylum accommodation contracts to allow siblings of the same sex to room-share to the age of 20; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","58478"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662974","Home Office","false","2017-01-09","<p>In considering the proposal to extend the current contracts the Home Office listened carefully to a range of interested parties, including the evidence that has been given to the Home Affairs Committee and direct feedback from non-governmental organisations’ through regular engagement activity with various stakeholder groups. In extending the contracts the Home Office took the opportunity to make improvements to the contracts that address the concerns that have been raised. We will continue to work closely with a range of stakeholders to continue to improve the operation of the contracts.</p><p>No changes have been made in relation to the requirements and restrictions on room sharing and the contract continues to require our contractors to comply with national legislation and local authority rules.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","58478 ; 58480 ; 58481 ; 58482","2017-01-09T18:04:05.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662974/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662974/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662974/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-20","Asylum: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what consultations took place with the National Asylum Seekers stakeholder forum and other interested parties on extending the contracts on asylum accommodation.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","58479"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662975","Home Office","false","2017-01-09","<p>The additional £10 million English language funding package for those who have been resettled under the Syrian Vulnerable Persons Resettlement and Vulnerable Children’s Resettlement schemes is available to the local authorities who support adults (age 19+). This funding comes jointly from the Department for Education’s Adult Education budget and from the Syrian Resettlement Programme budget and guidance on how to claim is being issued through the Strategic Migration Partnerships.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-01-09T18:14:13.883Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662975/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662975/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662975/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-20","Refugees: English Language","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, when the additional £10 million funding for English language teaching announced in September 2016 for refugees from the Syrian Vulnerable Person's Resettlement Scheme and the Vulnerable Children's Resettlement Scheme will be made available to those groups.","false","Biography information for Caroline Ansell","Eastbourne","Caroline Ansell","58368"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662976","Home Office","false","2017-01-09","<p>The Performance Reporting and Analysis Unit (PRAU) sends out the monthly Strategic Performance Report to the Performance and Ops board, the Chief Operating Officer and to the Regional Directors. In addition, PRAU also sends out the Monthly Queue to all regional directors.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-01-09T17:51:15.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662976/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662976/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662976/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-20","Immigration Controls","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what reports her Department has received on (a) staffing shortages and (b) waiting times at passport control at UK airports in the last three months; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","58372"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662977","Home Office","false","2017-01-17","<p>The Home Office collects and publishes data on firearm and shotgun certificates issued in England and Wales, including those granted and refused for new and renewal applications. The Government currently has no plans to collect and publish data on police performance in processing firearm and shotgun certificate applications. Under the Firearms Act 1968 firearm and shotgun certificate administration is a matter for the chief officer of police for the area in which the applicant lives.</p><p>In considering what information is collected and published by the Home Office, emphasis is given to whether data are justified, of strategic importance and able to be collected with minimal burden.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-01-17T14:19:42.583Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662977/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662977/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662977/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-20","Firearms: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer to the hon. Member for the Cotswolds of 1 December 2017 to Question 54884, for what reasons the Government does not collect or publish data on firearm and shotgun certificate applications.","false","Biography information for Mr Ian Liddell-Grainger","Bridgwater and West Somerset","Mr Ian Liddell-Grainger","58381"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662978","Home Office","false","2017-01-10","<p>The Minister of State for Policing and the Fire Service replied to right hon. Member in a letter dated 25 November 2016.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-01-10T15:41:43.877Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662978/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662978/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662978/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-20","Members: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, when she plans to respond to the letter from the hon. Member for Wolverhampton South West of 3 November 2016 on representation of the Special Constabulary, reference ZA5692.","false","Biography information for Rob Marris","Wolverhampton South West","Rob Marris","58386"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662979","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-01-13","We already have extra-territorial jurisdiction over some offences committed ostensibly to protect the ‘honour’ of a family or community, including the common law offence of murder, female genital mutilation and forced marriage. The Government has confirmed that it will bring forward legislative proposals to take extra-territorial jurisdiction over certain other offences that may be committed in this context, to comply with the requirements of the Istanbul Convention which the UK signed in June 2012. Where our courts do have jurisdiction, the investigation of alleged criminal offences is a matter for the police.","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-01-13T15:10:45.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662979/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662979/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662979/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-12-20","Honour Based Violence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what assessment the Government has made of the potential merits of bringing forward legislative proposals on extra-territorial effects for offences related to honour-based violence","false","Biography information for Kate Osamor","Edmonton","Kate Osamor","58579"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662980","Home Office","false","2017-01-09","<p>Work Permit arrangements ended in 2008 and were replaced by the Points Based System. The work permit database has been archived and there are no reporting facilities any longer on this database therefore data for 2006 and 2007 is not available.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-01-09T18:04:32.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662980/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662980/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662980/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-20","Work Permits: Africa","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many work permit applications have been approved for (a) doctors and (b) nurses and auxiliary nurses from (i) Nigeria, (ii) Ghana and (iii) other African countries in each year since 2007.","false","Biography information for Lord Lilley","Hitchin and Harpenden","Mr Peter Lilley","58592"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662981","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-01-13","We already have extra-territorial jurisdiction over some offences committed ostensibly to protect the ‘honour’ of a family or community, including the common law offence of murder, female genital mutilation and forced marriage. The Government has confirmed that it will bring forward legislative proposals to take extra-territorial jurisdiction over certain other offences that may be committed in this context, to comply with the requirements of the Istanbul Convention which the UK signed in June 2012. Where our courts do have jurisdiction, the investigation of alleged criminal offences is a matter for the police.","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-01-13T15:11:24.14Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662981/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662981/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662981/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-12-20","Honour Based Violence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the Government's plans are for investigating allegations of honour-based violence which are transnational.","false","Biography information for Kate Osamor","Edmonton","Kate Osamor","58580"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662982","Cabinet Office","false","2017-01-09","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p><p>On leaving the EU our intention is to create an immigration system that allows us to control the numbers of people coming from Europe in the future. But that does not mean closing the door to the brightest and the best and welcoming them to our country.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-01-09T16:29:05.823Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662982/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662982/answer","UKSA response to PQ58594 V.02.pdf","UKSA Response to Member - EU Nationals","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662982/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-12-20","EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many EU nationals are estimated to be (a) living and (b) working in the UK.","false","Biography information for Mr Pat McFadden","Wolverhampton South East","Mr Pat McFadden","58594"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662983","Home Office","false","2017-01-09","<p>Following Renfrewshire Council’s refusal of planning permission for a short term holding facility near Glasgow airport the Government is considering its position in relation to the right of appeal and any subsequent review of detention needs in Scotland.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-01-09T18:25:10.473Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662983/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662983/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662983/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-20","Immigrants: Detainees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, with reference to the letter from the Minister for Immigration to the Home Affairs Select Committee of 18 November 2016, what review of detention needs is taking place; and what the timescale is for that review.","false","Biography information for Gavin Newlands","Paisley and Renfrewshire North","Gavin Newlands","58597"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662984","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-01-27","<p>Data relating to compensation awarded in respect of convictions for human trafficking in 2015 can be found in the “outcomes by offence” data tool table contained in the annual Criminal Justice Statistics publication, linked below.</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/criminal-justice-system-statistics-quarterly-december-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/criminal-justice-system-statistics-quarterly-december-2015</a></p><p> </p><p>No defendants convicted in 2015 were ordered by the court to pay compensation for the offences of human trafficking for non-sexual exploitation and human trafficking for sexual exploitation.</p><p> </p><p>Under the Criminal Injuries Compensation Scheme 2012, compensation may be paid to victims of violent crime. However, these payments are on the basis of injury sustained and not related to criminal proceedings: the Criminal Injuries Compensation Authority which administers the scheme does not keep records based on convictions, and so cannot provide figures for the number of compensation payments made to victims of human trafficking.</p><p> </p><p>The Government has introduced provisions for bespoke Slavery and Trafficking Reparation Orders in the Modern Slavery Act 2015. These orders are designed to ensure that more money confiscated from convicted traffickers goes directly to their victims.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2017-01-27T14:13:29.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662984/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662984/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662984/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-12-20","Human Trafficking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many compensation awards of what amount were made to victims related to each of the 30 convictions for human trafficking recorded in 2015.","false","Biography information for Lord Garnier","Harborough","Sir Edward Garnier","58541"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662985","Home Office","false","2017-01-09","<p>As part of our work to evaluate the National Referral Mechanism pilot, we are looking at what data should be gathered in future.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-01-09T13:51:32.293Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662985/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662985/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662985/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-20","Human Trafficking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what plans she has to collect data on outcomes of victims of human trafficking referred to in the national referral mechanism after they have co-operated with police and provided evidence to assist with prosecutions.","false","Biography information for Lord Garnier","Harborough","Sir Edward Garnier","58540"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662986","Home Office","false","2017-01-10","<p>Published information on applications for short term study (previously referred to as 'student visitor') visas is published in table vi_01_q (Visa data tables volume 1) in 'Immigration Statistics, July-September 2016', available from the Home Office website at: https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/immigration-statistics-july-to-september-2016/list-of-tables</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-01-10T15:18:53.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662986/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662986/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662986/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-20","Visas: Overseas Students","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many students have been granted short-term study visas to study English in the UK in the last year for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Paul Scully","Sutton and Cheam","Paul Scully","58543"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662987","Home Office","false","2017-01-11","<p>Similar to the reviews which took place after the Nice attacks, the police and the security and intelligence agencies have reviewed security measures in place to ensure that there are robust plans and procedures in place to ensure the safety and security of the public from terrorist threats following the Berlin attack. This is a routine activity for the police and intelligence agencies, which is undertaken on a regular basis.</p><p>We continue to work with owners and operators of events and other crowded places sites to consider what more can be done to reduce vulnerabilities to vehicle attacks. We also regularly test our response to terrorist attacks, including learning the lessons from attacks like those we have seen recently in Germany and France, through national exercises which involve the Government, military, police, ambulance, fire and rescue service, and other agencies.</p><p>In addition we keep our preparedness under constant review, and looked again at our response following the terrorist attacks in Paris last year, delivering an uplift in our specialist response capability, including a £144 million programme over the next five years to uplift our armed policing resource.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2017-01-11T12:52:17Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662987/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662987/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662987/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-20","Terrorism: Motor Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether her Department intends to review security procedures in relation to terrorist attacks using vehicles following the attacks in Berlin on 19 December 2016.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","58577"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662988","Home Office","false","2017-01-11","<p>Following the Nice attack, the police and the security and intelligence agencies took steps to review our own security measures, to ensure that we had robust plans and procedures in place to ensure the safety and security of the public from terrorist threats.</p><p>All police forces reviewed upcoming events taking place in their regions to ensure that security measures were appropriate and proportionate in light of events in Nice, and intelligence and threat reporting. These operational activities (often working together with partner agencies) routinely seek to mitigate threats, or implement regimes to protect, detect and deter such attacks.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2017-01-11T12:53:32.07Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662988/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662988/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662988/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-20","Terrorism: Motor Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether her Department reviewed security procedures in relation to terrorist attacks using vehicles following the attacks in Nice in July 2016.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","58578"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662989","Home Office","false","2017-01-09","<p>In considering the proposal to extend the current contracts the Home Office listened carefully to a range of interested parties, including the evidence that has been given to the Home Affairs Committee and direct feedback from non-governmental organisations’ through regular engagement activity with various stakeholder groups. In extending the contracts the Home Office took the opportunity to make improvements to the contracts that address the concerns that have been raised. We will continue to work closely with a range of stakeholders to continue to improve the operation of the contracts.</p><p>No changes have been made in relation to the requirements and restrictions on room sharing and the contract continues to require our contractors to comply with national legislation and local authority rules.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","58478 ; 58479 ; 58481 ; 58482","2017-01-09T18:04:05.99Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662989/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662989/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662989/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-20","Asylum: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what consultations took place with the National Asylum Seekers stakeholder forum and other interested parties on changing the sharing criteria in asylum accommodation contracts to allow siblings of opposite sex to room-share to the age of 16; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","58480"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662990","Home Office","false","2017-01-10","<p>The Department does not publish part year financial data nor does it record or hold data in the specific way requested. Details of Departmental and ALB spend and planned spend on (a) Staffing, (b) other revenue costs and (c) capital expenditure are detailed by financial from 2011-12 through to 2019-20 can be found in the Home Office “Core Data Tables”. However this is not held or published by region.</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/539813/CoreDataTables-Gov_ods.ods</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-01-10T18:04:31.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662990/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662990/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662990/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-20","Home Office: Yorkshire and the Humber","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how much her Department and its arms-length departmental bodies have spent on (a) staffing, (b) other revenue costs and (c) capital expenditure in the current fiscal year in Yorkshire and the Humber.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","58504"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662991","Home Office","false","2017-01-17","<p>We do not routinely comment on individual immigration cases. An application for asylum can only be made by a person who is present in the United Kingdom</p><p>The transfer of Mr Mingazov from the detention facility is a matter for the US Government.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2017-01-17T17:22:22.997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662991/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662991/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662991/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-20","Ravil Mingazov","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether the Government has received an application from Ravil Mingazov for asylum since she has been granted release from Guantanamo Bay.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","58526"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662992","Home Office","false","2017-01-10","<p>The Home Office does not hold the information requested centrally. This is an operational mater for the police and other partner agencies.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","58619 ; 58621","2017-01-10T15:40:14.14Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662992/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662992/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662992/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-20","Driving Tests: Personation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many people have been investigated by police forces for impersonating a candidate and taking their written or practical driving test for them by police force area in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Karl McCartney","Lincoln","Karl McCartney","58620"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662993","Home Office","false","2017-01-10","<p>I am sorry but this information is not available and could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-01-10T15:34:31.18Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662993/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662993/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662993/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-20","Parliamentary and Health Service Ombudsman","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what information her Department holds on the total amount of compensation payments it has made at the request of the Parliamentary and Health Service Ombudsman in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Naz Shah","Bradford West","Naz Shah","58589"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662994","Home Office","false","2017-01-10","<p>The Home Office does not hold the information requested centrally. This is an operational mater for the police and other partner agencies.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","58620 ; 58621","2017-01-10T15:40:14.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662994/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662994/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662994/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-20","Driving: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what checks are made to ensure that people convicted of using an impersonator to take a written or practical driving test do not continue to drive using a fraudulently obtained driving licence.","false","Biography information for Karl McCartney","Lincoln","Karl McCartney","58619"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662995","Home Office","false","2017-01-10","<p>In March 2016 we published our Violence against Women and Girls (VAWG) Strategy for 2016-2020, which sets out an ambitious programme of reform, supported by increased funding of £80 million.</p><p>As set out in the Strategy, from April 2017 we will move from supporting individual Independent Domestic Violence Advisers (IDVA) and multi-agency risk assessment conference (MARAC) coordinator posts, to a model of supporting community-led services which encourage new approaches through the £15 million VAWG Service Transformation Fund which was announced on 7 December 2016.</p><p>This will help promote better collaboration and joint leadership, encourage new approaches incorporating early intervention, and establish and embed the best ways to help victims, survivors and their families. We have consulted widely with the voluntary and community sector and statutory stakeholders in the development of both the strategy and the Transformation Fund and we will continue to work with the women’s sector to monitor the level of IDVA and MARAC provision.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton","58623","2017-01-10T17:57:21.693Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662995/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662995/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662995/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-20","Domestic Abuse","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what her policy is on continuing direct grant funding from her Department to support independent domestic violence advisers and multi-agency risk assessment conference coordinators after March 2017.","false","Biography information for Sarah Champion","Rotherham","Sarah Champion","58622"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662996","Home Office","false","2017-01-09","<p>I am sorry, but the information is not centrally recorded and to provide you with this information would exceed the cost limit, at disproportionate cost.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-01-09T17:42:46.97Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662996/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662996/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662996/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-20","Immigration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what information her Department holds on how much compensation has been paid as a result of the mis-administration of applications for indefinite leave to remain in 2015.","false","Biography information for Naz Shah","Bradford West","Naz Shah","58590"
