"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661776","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-01-09","<p>The Northern Ireland Office recognises the importance of embedding diversity in everything it does. The Permanent Secretary of the NIO, Sir Jonathan Stephens KCB is the overall Diversity Champion at board level.</p><p> </p><p>The PUS is supported in his role as NIO Diversity Champion by the Department’s two directors who champion a number of specific diversity categories. Further details are provided below:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>NIO Director</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Diversity Category Championed</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Colin Perry</p></td><td><p><ul><li>Black and Minority Ethnic</li><li>Lesbian, Gay, Bi-sexual and Transgender</li></ul></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Mark Larmour</p></td><td><p><ul><li>Disability</li><li>Other protected characteristics</li></ul></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"2017-01-09T11:41:21.16Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661776/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661776/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661776/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2016-12-19","Northern Ireland Office: Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, who the diversity champion is on his departmental board.","false","Biography information for Paula Sherriff","Dewsbury","Paula Sherriff","58241"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661777","Prime Minister","false","2017-01-13","<p>I refer my hon. Friend to the answer I gave to the right hon. Member for Leicester East (Mr Vaz) on 16 December 2016, UIN 56583.</p>","Maidenhead","Mrs Theresa May",,"2017-01-13T09:33:21.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661777/answer","Biography information for Mrs Theresa May","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661777/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661777/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2016-12-19","Yemen: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, whether she discussed the conflict in Yemen with the Saudi government on (a) 15 September and (b) 7 December 2016.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","58301"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661779","Prime Minister","false","2017-01-13","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the Statement made by the Secretary of State for Defence, my right hon. Friend the Member for Sevenoaks (Mr Fallon) on 19 December 2016, Official Report, column 1215-1227.</p>","Maidenhead","Mrs Theresa May",,"2017-01-13T09:34:19.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661779/answer","Biography information for Mrs Theresa May","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661779/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661779/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2016-12-19","Saudi Arabia: Ammunition","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, what discussions she has had with the Saudi government on its possession of internationally prohibited munitions.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","58302"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661780","Prime Minister","false","2017-01-09","<p>As is normal for a European Council, I had meetings and conversations with a number of European leaders in the course of the December Council in Brussels.</p><p>In particular, I had bilateral meetings with Dalia Grybauskaite, the President of Lithuania, Maris Kucinskis, the Prime Minister of Latvia and with Martin Schulz, President of the European Parliament and Guy Verhofstadt MEP.</p>","Maidenhead","Mrs Theresa May",,"2017-01-09T15:04:01.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661780/answer","Biography information for Mrs Theresa May","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661780/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661780/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2016-12-19","European Council","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, whether she had any individual meetings with (a) leaders and (b) officials from other EU member states during her visit to Brussels for the European Council meeting in December.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","58228"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661781","Scotland Office","false","2017-01-11","<p>I place great importance on the Scotland Office’s commitment to Diversity. The governance of the Scotland Office and the Office of the Advocate General is overseen by the Offices’ Joint Management Board, which I chair. The Diversity Champions on the Board are Francesca Osowska, Director of the Scotland Office, and Michael Chalmers, Director of the Office of the Advocate General.</p><p> </p><p>The Government introduced Diversity Champions as part of the Talent Action Plan commitment to have champions in all departments.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2017-01-11T13:09:43.243Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661781/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661781/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661781/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2016-12-19","Scotland Office: Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, who the diversity champion is on his departmental board.","false","Biography information for Paula Sherriff","Dewsbury","Paula Sherriff","58242"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661782","Scotland Office","false","2017-01-11","<p>I refer the hon Member to my answers of 14 December 2016 (UINs 56910 and 56916) and 20 December 2016 (UIN 57929).</p><p> </p><p>For JobCentre Plus offices over three miles or 20 minutes away by public transport, DWP are carrying out local consultation prior to implementing any changes to help inform decisions about additional provision, such as outreach services. The consultation is available online and through the affected Jobcentres. This consultation was launched immediately after the announcements were made, and is open until 31 January. Staff will also advise customers on alternative Jobcentre locations, taking into account travel and access to the local labour market.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell","58156","2017-01-11T13:11:08.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661782/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661782/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661782/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2016-12-19","Jobcentres: Glasgow","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what discussions he has had with the Scottish Government regarding jobcentre closure proposals for Glasgow.","false","Biography information for Stewart Malcolm McDonald","Glasgow South","Stewart Malcolm McDonald","58152"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661783","Scotland Office","false","2017-01-11","<p>I refer the hon Member to my answers of 14 December 2016 (UINs 56910 and 56916) and 20 December 2016 (UIN 57929).</p><p> </p><p>For JobCentre Plus offices over three miles or 20 minutes away by public transport, DWP are carrying out local consultation prior to implementing any changes to help inform decisions about additional provision, such as outreach services. The consultation is available online and through the affected Jobcentres. This consultation was launched immediately after the announcements were made, and is open until 31 January. Staff will also advise customers on alternative Jobcentre locations, taking into account travel and access to the local labour market.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell","58152","2017-01-11T13:11:09.023Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661783/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661783/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661783/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2016-12-19","Department for Work and Pensions: Glasgow","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, whether his Office was consulted by the Department for Work and Pensions (DWP) on its proposals for the reduction of DWP estate in Glasgow.","false","Biography information for Stewart Malcolm McDonald","Glasgow South","Stewart Malcolm McDonald","58156"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661784","Scotland Office","false","2017-01-11","<p>The UK Government is committed to retaining an accessible Jobcentre network to serve customers in all areas of the country. We will also continue working with the Scottish Government to support disabled people in Scotland.</p><p> </p><p>Castlemilk is one of the three JobCentre Plus offices in Glasgow where DWP are carrying out local consultation prior to implementing any changes to help inform decisions about additional provision, such as outreach services. The consultation is available online and through the affected Jobcentres and was launched immediately after the announcements were made. The consultation is open until 31 January and the Minister for Employment also met with Glasgow MPs recently to discuss their concerns. Staff in the affected Jobcentres, which includes both Castlemilk and Langside, will also advise customers on alternative Jobcentre locations, taking into account travel and access to the local labour market.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2017-01-11T13:13:04.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661784/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661784/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661784/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2016-12-19","Jobcentres: Glasgow","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what discussions he has had with representatives  of the Scottish Government on support for disabled people who currently rely on services at Castlemilk and Langside jobcentres.","false","Biography information for Stewart Malcolm McDonald","Glasgow South","Stewart Malcolm McDonald","58155"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661785","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-11","<p>The Government has no financial stake or control in Eurostar, which is a private company.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-01-11T14:21:01.99Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661785/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661785/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661785/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-19","Eurostar","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what stake or degree of control the Government retains in Eurostar.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","58166"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661786","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-09","<p>The European Communities Act will be repealed on the day we leave the European Union – meaning that the authority of EU law in Britain will end. We will convert the body of existing EU law into domestic law and Parliament will be free to amend, repeal and improve any law it chooses.</p><p> </p><p>This process will give businesses and workers maximum certainty as we leave the European Union. And we are absolutely clear: existing workers’ legal rights will continue to be guaranteed in law.</p><p> </p><p>The maritime sector is, of course, being considered as part of the Government’s work developing an overall approach to negotiations.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-01-09T12:27:28.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661786/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661786/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661786/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-19","Shipping","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of legislative changes required for (a) the shipping industry, (b) the ports sector and (c) UK seafarers and dock workers once the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","58146"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661787","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-09","<p>The European Communities Act will be repealed on the day we leave the European Union – meaning that the authority of EU law in Britain will end. We will convert the body of existing EU law into domestic law and Parliament will be free to amend, repeal and improve any law it chooses.</p><p> </p><p>This process will give businesses and workers maximum certainty as we leave the European Union. And we are absolutely clear: existing workers’ legal rights will continue to be guaranteed in law.</p><p> </p><p>The maritime sector is, of course, being considered as part of the Government’s work developing an overall approach to negotiations.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-01-09T12:32:27.403Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661787/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661787/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661787/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-19","Shipping","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what discussions he has had with ministerial colleagues on legislative changes required for the maritime services sector once the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","58147"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661788","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-09","<p>The European Communities Act will be repealed on the day we leave the European Union – meaning that the authority of EU law in Britain will end. We will convert the body of existing EU law into domestic law and Parliament will be free to amend, repeal and improve any law it chooses.</p><p> </p><p>This process will give businesses and workers maximum certainty as we leave the European Union. And we are absolutely clear: existing workers’ legal rights will continue to be guaranteed in law.</p><p> </p><p>The maritime sector is, of course, being considered as part of the Government’s work developing an overall approach to negotiations.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-01-09T12:37:54.933Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661788/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661788/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661788/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-19","Shipping","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what his Department's priorities will be for the maritime sector in negotiations with other EU countries before the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","58148"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661789","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-10","<p>The Permanent Secretary, Philip Rutnam, is the Department for Transport’s (DfT’s) corporate Diversity Champion on the Departmental Board and is accountable for the delivery of the DfT Equality Objectives. He is supported by Directors General and Agency Chief Executives, who champion the specific Protected Characteristics of sex, race, age, disability, sexual orientation, pregnancy &amp; maternity, marriage &amp; civil partnership, transgender, and religion &amp; belief.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-01-10T15:54:37.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661789/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661789/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661789/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-19","Department for Transport: Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, who the diversity champion is on his departmental board.","false","Biography information for Paula Sherriff","Dewsbury","Paula Sherriff","58243"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661790","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-09","<p>The Maritime and Coastguard Agency (MCA) is implementing changes so that they can operate in a more effective, efficient and commercial manner, with respect to ship survey and inspection activities. This follows the public consultation on estates laydown and organisational structure. The MCA has completed its dialogue with trade union representatives and a formal offer in relation to pay, terms and conditions has been made. That offer is now subject of a union ballot that closes on 13 January.</p><p> </p><p>In terms of the fees that the MCA charges for its services, officials are developing a revised fee structure in light of the recent separate consultation on this matter. I expect the revised fee structure to be in place in the first half of 2017.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-01-09T11:27:13.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661790/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661790/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661790/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-19","Maritime and Coastguard Agency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, with reference to paragraphs 4.82 to 4.84 of the Maritime Growth Study: Keeping the UK competitive in a global market, published 7 September 2015, what actions the Maritime and Coastguard Agency (MCA) has taken to implement the conclusions of the Survey and Inspection Transformation Programme (SITP); and which conclusions from the SITP currently await implementation by the MCA.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","58107"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661791","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-09","<p>Network Rail is delivering the Great Western Electrification Programme to the dates set out in Sir Peter Hendy’s report published on 25 November 2015. This includes completing electrification of the Great Western Mainline to Cardiff by December 2018.</p><p> </p><p>For the sections of electrification due for completion in Control Period 6 (CP6) (2019-2024), including the four sections which were deferred in November 2016, delivery schedules will be agreed as part of Network Rail’s CP6 planning process.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-01-09T12:09:17.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661791/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661791/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661791/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-19","Great Western Railway Line: Electrification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when he expects the Great Western Railway electrification scheme to be completed.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","58103"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661792","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-11","<p>The Department for Transport do not hold any information relating to the number of Eurostar operating days affected by people on the track.</p><p> </p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-01-11T14:28:42.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661792/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661792/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661792/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-19","Channel Tunnel: Undocumented Migrants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many Eurostar operating days in each of the last five years have been affected by people on the track.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","58164"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661793","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-11","<p>The UK Channel Tunnel terminal and associated Eurotunnel shuttle services are policed by Kent Police and the costs are directly billed to Eurotunnel. The Department for Transport does not hold information on the cost of these services.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-01-11T14:25:56.19Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661793/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661793/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661793/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-19","Eurotunnel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the cost has been of policing the Eurotunnel and its associated rail services in each of the last five years  .","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","58165"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661794","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-11","<p>Eurostar is a GB licensed railway undertaking regulated by the Office of Rail and Road. Full background information on the licensing and operating requirements can be found on the website of the Office of Rail and Road at the following address:</p><p><a href="http://orr.gov.uk/what-and-how-we-regulate/licensing/licensing-railway-operators" target="_blank">http://orr.gov.uk/what-and-how-we-regulate/licensing/licensing-railway-operators</a></p><p> </p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-01-11T14:31:51.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661794/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661794/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661794/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-19","Eurostar","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what responsibility the Office of Rail and Road has for regulating the operation of Eurostar.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","58163"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661795","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-09","<p>There have been three external consultancies which have carried out work to implement the recommendations of the Maritime Growth Study. They are:</p><p> </p><p>KPMG consultancy services undertook an analysis of commercial opportunities within the Maritime and Coastguard Agency at a cost of £207,744.00 (inclusive of VAT). It reported on 14 September 2016.</p><p> </p><p>Oxford Economics undertook a review to update its assessment of the requirement for seafarers in the UK maritime sector at a cost of £113,238 (inclusive of VAT). It reported on 31<sup>st</sup> October 2016.</p><p> </p><p>Frazer-Nash with Oxford Economics undertook a review of Support for Maritime Training (SMarT) funding at a cost of £122,287 (inclusive of VAT). It reported on 31<sup>st</sup> December 2016.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-01-09T11:33:35.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661795/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661795/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661795/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-19","Department for Transport: Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will name each of the external consultants contracted by his Department to carry out work to implement the recommendations of the Maritime Growth Study since September 2015; and what the (a) completion date and (b) value is of each such contract.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","58094"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661796","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-09","<p>This was an unfortunate accident. My Rt Hon Friend the Secretary of State got out of the car, checked the cyclist was okay and waited until he was back on his feet. He spoke to the cyclist and apologised; they shook hands. No details were requested at the time by either party. The Secretary of State has since been in contact with the cyclist and the matter is closed.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-01-09T14:36:22.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661796/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661796/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661796/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-19","Cycling: Accidents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, for what reasons he did not exchange his details with the cyclist whom he was involved in a road incident with on 12 October 2016.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","58090"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661798","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-09","<p>The incident was reported on 12 October following normal procedure.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-01-09T14:45:16.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661798/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661798/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661798/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-19","Cycling: Accidents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether the incident between him and a cyclist on 12 October 2016 was reported to his Department's Permanent Secretary.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","58091"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661799","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-13","<p>We have continually urged all sides to get back around the negotiating table and end this dispute which is causing immense pain and misery for thousands of hard working commuters. In December last year the Secretary of State offered to meet with the unions to try and help resolve this dispute. He repeated this offer in a letter to the unions in January. However we have yet to receive a reply indicating that they are willing to suspend the strikes and meet.</p><p> </p><p>Ministers and officials have been working tirelessly to try and find a way through this dispute, but the unions appear to have little interest in any resolution that does not involve a full roll-back of modern working practices which includes the introduction of new trains.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-01-13T10:08:21.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661799/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661799/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661799/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-19","Southern: Industrial Disputes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps the Government is taking to support a resolution of the dispute between Southern Rail and the Rail, Maritime and Transport Union.","false","Biography information for Ian Lavery","Wansbeck","Ian Lavery","58250"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661800","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-01-17","<p>Parking policy is shared between DfT and DCLG. 72 people in my Department work on cities and local growth as part of a joint Cities and Local Growth Unit with BEIS. These are DCLG posts. The unit covers a range of policy areas including devolution, regeneration and reforms to off-street car parking.</p><p>The discussion paper last year entitled ‘Parking reform: tackling unfair practices’, sought thoughts and comments on the private parking sector. A summary of the responses was made available on 11 May 2016 by my Department. I am considering responses to the discussion paper, and options for further reform.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-01-17T17:35:46.93Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661800/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661800/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661800/answer","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661800/answer/previousversion/29824",,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-12-19","Parking: Unfair Practices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many civil servants are working on his Department's response to the consultation, Parking reform: tackling unfair practices.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","58287"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661801","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-13","<p>As the Parliamentary Under Secretary of State for Transport I am responsible for cycling. I last met with organisations representing cyclists on 14 November 2016 and will be meeting with the All-Party Parliamentary Cycling Group in a few weeks.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-01-13T09:39:45.88Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661801/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661801/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661801/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-19","Cycling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what discussions he has had with organisations representing cyclists since his appointment.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","58191"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661802","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-13","<p>The Government is fully committed to creating a safe environment for all road users, and in particular vulnerable road users such as cyclists and pedestrians.</p><p> </p><p>In September we launched a cycle safety campaign targeting both cyclists and lorry drivers to raise awareness of the dangers of being alongside a lorry turning left. The campaign ran in London and Manchester – cities with the highest number of cyclist fatalities involving a lorry.</p><p> </p><p>We are also working on wider cyclist safety in other ways, including changes to vehicle design, mandatory training for HGV drivers and optional training for cyclists, including extending the Bikeability programme of cycle training. Bikeability provides trainees with riding skills suited to the road, but also explains the importance of obeying the Highway Code, the correct use of safety equipment, and sharing the road with other people.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-01-13T09:43:01.413Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661802/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661802/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661802/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-19","Cycling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps he has taken to improve safety for cyclists since his appointment.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","58192"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661803","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-09","<p>We remain committed to improving station accessibility and have continued with the Access for All programme, launched in 2006. All of the available Access for All funding is allocated until at least 2019. Should further funding become available in the future we will commission new nominations for projects.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, whenever infrastructure work is carried out at a station by the industry, it must comply with the relevant EU and UK standards. These can be found at <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/publications/accessible-railway-stations-design-standards" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/accessible-railway-stations-design-standards</a>. My Rt Hon Friend may therefore wish to contact Network Rail to see if any work is planned at Brookmans Park that might trigger these requirements.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-01-09T12:20:59.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661803/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661803/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661803/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-19","Railway Stations: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will make representations to Network Rail to ensure that it adds disabled access routes into (a) Brookmans Park railway station and (b) other suburban railway stations with limited access.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","58270"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661804","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-11","<p>The franchise agreement contains incentive/penalty regimes to encourage operators to meet/exceed the performance targets. Where, despite these regimes there are performance issues, the Department takes a stepped approach to managing any failure of a franchised train operator to deliver its franchise obligations, taking account of factors such as the impact on passengers and taxpayers, in line with its published enforcement policy. Sanctions may include requiring the operator to implement a remedial plan to provide redress, a financial penalty, or in the most extreme cases removal of the franchise.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-01-11T12:01:20.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661804/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661804/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661804/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-19","Railways: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what criteria his Department uses when assessing whether to withdraw a franchise from a consistently poorly-performing railway operator.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","58266"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661805","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-11","<p>The Department takes a stepped approach to managing any failure of a franchised train operator to deliver its franchise obligations, taking account of factors such as the impact on passengers and taxpayers, in line with its published enforcement policy, which can be found here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/529553/enforcement-policy-rail-franchise-agreements-and-closures.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/529553/enforcement-policy-rail-franchise-agreements-and-closures.pdf</a></p><p> </p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-01-11T12:05:07.04Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661805/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661805/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661805/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-19","Railways: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what sanctions other than franchise withdrawal his Department has used to hold poorly performing railway operators to account.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","58267"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661806","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-10","<p>Network Rail is delivering the Great Western Electrification Programme to the dates set out in Sir Peter Hendy’s report published on 25 November 2015. This includes completing electrification of the Great Western Mainline to Cardiff by December 2018.</p><p> </p><p>For the sections of electrification due for completion in Control Period 6 (CP6) (2019-2024), including the four sections which were deferred in November 2016, delivery schedules will be agreed as part of Network Rail’s CP6 planning process.</p><p> </p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-01-10T15:45:34.053Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661806/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661806/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661806/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-19","Great Western Railway Line: Electrification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the timetable is for the completion of the Great Western Railway's electrification scheme; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","58269"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661807","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-11","<p>The National Express East Coast franchise was withdrawn by the Department on the basis of failure to deliver its franchise obligations.</p><p> </p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-01-11T12:08:14.59Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661807/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661807/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661807/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-19","Railways: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, under what circumstances a railway franchise has been withdrawn from a poorly performing operator; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","58268"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661808","Department for Transport","false","2017-01-09","<p>The Department does not budget or forecast on a regional basis, as such this information is not available for the current financial year.</p><p> </p><p>Information on the total amount of current and capital expenditure on services by organisation in Yorkshire and the Humber is publically available on gov.uk as part of the Country and Regional Analysis statistical release. It contains spending on current and capital expenditure on services by organisation, but not down to the level of staff expenditure. This information covers 2011-12 through to 2015-16 and can be found at the following web link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/country-and-regional-analysis-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/country-and-regional-analysis-2016</a></p><p><em> </em></p><p>This data can be accessed by using either the ‘interactive tables’ or the ‘database’. The relevant information for 2015-16 is reproduced below;</p><p><strong> </strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>2015-16 outturn (£’m)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>DfT</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Current (b)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Capital (c)</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Yorkshire and Humber</p></td><td><p>£1,397m</p></td><td><p>£489m</p></td><td><p>£908m</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-01-09T11:02:10.183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661808/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661808/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661808/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-19","Department for Transport: Yorkshire and the Humber","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate he has made of the value of (a) staffing expenditure, (b) other revenue costs and (c) capital expenditure by his Department and its arms-length bodies in whole or in part in Yorkshire and the Humber in 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","58316"
