"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661869","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-01-13","<p>The Department has appointed Catherine Webb as the dedicated senior equalities champion who sits on the Department's Executive Board and provides an insight for all protected characteristics. The Department for Exiting the European Union is committed to the creation of a diverse and inclusive working environment to ensure staff do not face any barriers to success, and all staff feel supported at work. As such, the Department is committed to the steps established in the 2016 Talent Action Plan to help the Civil Service become the most inclusive employer in the UK. The department is also committed to working with a diverse range of external organisations, to ensure our work reflects a broad range of opinions across the UK.</p><p> </p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones",,"2017-01-13T12:40:58.63Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661869/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661869/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/661869/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-12-19","Department for Exiting the European Union: Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, who the diversity champion is on his departmental board.","false","Biography information for Paula Sherriff","Dewsbury","Paula Sherriff","58235"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662021","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-12-22","<p>As the then Home Secretary explained in her speech of 23rd March 2015, British values – such as regard for the rule of law, participation in and acceptance of democracy, equality, free speech and respect for minorities – are supported by the overwhelming majority of British people. They are sustained by our most important local and national institutions. And they are the means by which we have made our multi-racial, multi-cultural and multi-religious society succeed.</p>",,"Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","HL4192 ; HL4193","2016-12-22T16:11:01.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662021/answer","Biography information for Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662021/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/662021/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-12-19","National Identity","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, in the light of reports that civil servants and other holders of public office might be required to swear an oath to British values, what is their definition of British values.","false","Biography information for Lord Ahmed",,"Lord Ahmed","HL4191"
